main event: A bright whitish object with occasional green and/or red lights was observed over Shallop Cove, Newfoundland, on August 24, 1965.
interesting points: The object was not as bright as the morning star,It moved in a smooth straight path at extremely high altitude,It was sighted by Mr. George Neuhold and 7 family members,Similar objects were reported on the two previous days,The sighting lasted for about three minutes and occurred at approximately 1:30 AM.
sighted object: a bright whitish object with occasional green and/or red lights
witness description: Mr. George Neuhold, 45, a slot machine mechanic and carpenter
